The paper discusses the use of Software Defined Networking (SDN) in mobile ad hoc networks for tactical operations. This topic falls under the category of computer networks (cs.NI) and network security and cryptography (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the challenges of the ad hoc and coalition network environment, which relates to information theory (cs.IT) and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). Finally, the paper proposes novel architecture designs, which falls under the category of multiagent systems (cs.MA).
